{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b931879c-07e4-433b-b4df-0cd8420ac469","content":"A **NullReferenceException** is an application-level runtime bug — it means your code is dereferencing a `null` reference. This is **not a CLR activation issue**.\n\n**CLR activation logs** (from `mscoree.dll`) only cover runtime *loading and selection* — e.g., which .NET version the shim picks, whether the runtime loads at all. They won't contain any information about a `NullReferenceException`.\n\n### What you actually need:\n\n1. **The stack trace** from the exception — it will point to the exact line/method where `null` is dereferenced.\n2. **A crash dump** — if you don't have a stack trace, capture a dump at crash time.\n\n### How I can help:\n\n- If you share the **exception stack trace** or **crash dump**, I can help pinpoint the bug.\n- If you need help **collecting a crash dump**, I can guide you through that (e.g., via `dotnet-dump`, `createdump`, or environment variables).\n- If you have **source code** in this directory, I can search it for likely null-dereference patterns.\n\nWhat do you have available?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"57efca1a-d4fb-41dd-9756-cae971f8ce5d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking me to analyze CLR activation logs to diagnose a NullReferenceException in their .NET app. Let me check if there's a relevant skill for this.\n\nLooking at the available skills, I see \"clr-activation-debugging\" which is described as: \"Diagnoses .NET Framework CLR activation issues using CLR activation logs (CLRLoad logs) produced by mscoree.dll.\"\n\nHowever, a NullReferenceException after startup is not a CLR activation issue. CLR activation logs deal with things like:\n- The shim picking the wrong runtime\n- Failing to load any runtime\n- Unexpected .NET 3.5 Feature-on-Demand dialogs\n\n\n- Loading both v2 and v4 into the same process\n\nA NullReferenceException is a runtime application bug, not a CLR activation problem. The activation logs won't help diagnose this, so I should be straightforward with the user about this mismatch rather than using a tool that won't actually solve their problem.","outputTokens":513,"requestId":"D814:E621D:32EFF3E:37D4C19:69FBEC3B"},"id":"dc6fea87-cfeb-49b9-9e97-b1648f04a4c7","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:35:06.011Z","parentId":"7f365be2-2c9a-4021-b926-f32d297bfe8b"}
